Package commands

Contains all the abstract and concrete commands used by the GUI. There exists exactly one command for each of the command sections in the official Player documentation.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PlayerCommand
    Abstract class which represents commands that may be issued to the Player.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CellCharCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~disp-cell-char command in the player.
    CellLowerCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~disp-cell-lower command in the player.
    CellRaiseCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~disp-cell-raise command in the player.
    ClearAllCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~disp-cellAll command in the player.
    ClearCellCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~disp-clear-cell command in the player.
    GoHereCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the jump tags in the player.
    PauseCommand
    A class to represent pause commands.
    QuestionCommand  
    RepeatButtonCommand
    A class to represent button repeating commands.
    RepeatCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~repeat command in the player.
    ResetButtonCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~reset-buttons command in the player.
    SetPinsCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~disp-cell-pins command in the player.
    SetStringCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~disp-string command in the player.
    SetVoiceCommand
    A class to represent set voice commands.
    SkipButtonCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~skip-button command in the player.
    SkipCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~skip command in the player.
    SoundCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~sound command in the player.
    TTSCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the TTS command in the player.
    UserInputCommand
    Command wrapper to represent the /~user-input command in the player.
